			<ns0:name>mcgra...@chromium.org</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/109286297231979736865/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">Due to http://code.google.com/p/nativeclient/issues/detail?id=2221
we will cease allowing the x86-64 string instructions.

Moreover, these instructions never add in %r15 regardless of what operands you write in the assembly code.  So code using these is accessing the wrong memory.

Such instructions are used in some glibc assembly code, notably string functions and dl-trampoline.S.
